# cvvdp Path A Phase 1b measurement (2026-05-26)
#
# Run command:
#   cargo run --release --example mem_mode_b_vs_full -p cvvdp-gpu --features cuda
#
# Git commit: c73cc47e4d8e (Path A Phase 1b wire — Weber strip walker reads per-strip upscaled_c_strip)
# Branch: master (workspace zenmetrics--cvvdp-path-a-phase1b)
# Hostname: water-cooled AMD Ryzen 9 7950X / RTX-class CUDA
# Driver: nvidia-smi runtime 13.2
# h_body = 256 (subprocess-per-cell — pool reset between Full and Mode B)
#
# Methodology: subprocess-per-measurement (parent process samples
# nvidia-smi memory.used during compute_dkl_jod child run; child
# exits releasing the cubecl pool to the driver).
#
# Columns:
#   estimate_master_mib — pre-Path-B-chunk-1 analytical estimate (Full reference)
#   estimate_head_mib   — post-Phase-1b analytical estimate
#                          (estimate_gpu_memory_bytes for Full,
#                           estimate_gpu_memory_bytes_strip_pair for Mode B)
#   nvsmi_delta_mib     — nvidia-smi memory.used delta during child run
#   jod                 — JOD score returned by compute_dkl_jod
#
# Key findings:
#
#   1. JOD BIT-IDENTICAL between Full and Mode B at both 1024² and
#      4096² (|diff| = 0.000000). The Phase 1b kernel + dispatch
#      changes leave the metric output exactly unchanged.
#
#   2. nvsmi_delta_mib unchanged at MiB precision — the analytical
#      ~12 MiB savings (per-strip upscaled_c_strip at 1024²,
#      h_body=256) is below cubecl pool over-allocation granularity.
#      The task brief noted this would happen ("even 5-10 MiB delta
#      is acceptable for Phase 1b — the goal is to land the
#      architecture"). Driver-level measurability arrives once
#      multiple Phase 1b-class buffers shrink in tandem (vscratch_c,
#      bands_dis, etc.) and the pool ceiling drops below the next
#      cubecl page-rounding boundary.
#
#   3. estimate_head_mib for Mode B shows 57 MiB at 1024² and 373 MiB
#      at 4096², compared to the Full estimator's 178 / 2858 MiB.
#      That number is the ASPIRATIONAL Phase-A target — the
#      estimator already models per-strip allocation for ALL the
#      strip-aware buffers (bands_ref, bands_dis, gauss_ref, the
#      full weber_scratch); Phase 1b shrinks only upscaled_c. The
#      gap between current driver nvsmi (385 MiB) and the
#      aspirational estimate (57 MiB) is the remaining Path-A work
#      tracked in subsequent phases.
#
# Analytical per-strip savings (h_body = 256, 1024² Mode B):
#
#   level | fine_w | strip_h_at_k | bytes saved (3 channels)
#       0 |  1024  |     256      |     9 437 184 B
#       1 |   512  |     128      |     2 359 296 B
#       2 |   256  |      64      |       589 824 B
#       3 |   128  |      32      |       147 456 B
#       4 |    64  |      16      |        36 864 B
#       5 |    32  |       8      |         9 216 B
#       ---- total ----                  12 579 840 B = 11.999 MiB
#
# All Phase-1b gates pass:
#   - cargo check -p cvvdp-gpu --features cuda: clean
#   - strip_kernel_parity_pyramid (5/5 incl. new src_strip_offset test)
#   - strip_mode_b_parity (6/6 incl. mode_b_score_matches_full_64x64)
#   - mode_b_walker_parity (7/7 incl. mode_b_walker_jod_matches_full_at_1024_h_body_256)
#   - memory_mode umbrella (13/13)
#
# Pre-existing master failures unrelated to Phase 1b (also fail on
# the parent commit a17713248d1b before this work):
#   - cpu_backend::compute_dkl_jod_host_pool_matches_pycvvdp_at_73x91_odd_on_cpu_backend
#     (cubecl-cpu atomic<f32> non-determinism; master varies 7.74-7.88 JOD).
#   - strip_mode_e_parity::mode_e_strip_h_body_explicit_override
#     (ModeUnsupported("Strip { h_body=invalid }") — unrelated mode).
